Recommended server system Cisco UCS.
VoIP from Cisco as well, extra synergy from both.
350 workstations, 800 users, on a VDI system.
Hooked up to Storage area network.
-	Climate control: find wattage to BTUs (British Thermal Units) with some added overhead, tonnage of cooling needed, redundant Air Conditioning which can both carry the full load.
-	Redundant power: UPS which can carry the load of all critical equipment for >= 15 minutes. Generators behind that.
-	Fire Handling: Fire rated doors, walls, intumescent sealant.
-	Disaster prevention/handling: water aversion, location of conditioning units, ceiling loads
